# Database Changes Must Use Migrations

**NEVER** tell the user to run SQL manually, use the Supabase dashboard, or apply database changes by hand.
This project has a full migration pipeline (`supabase/migrations/`).

Any SQL that needs to run against the database — schema changes, data fixes, backfills, function updates — **must** be written as a new migration file:

```bash
npx supabase migration new <descriptive_name>
```

Then write the SQL in the generated file under `supabase/migrations/`.

This includes one-time data fixes, `auth.users` metadata updates, RLS policy changes, and stored function modifications. No exceptions.
